Software Architecture

1. One-Tier
2. Two-Tier
3. Three-Tier
4. N-Tier

Tier: Server: Layer

Server: The server serves the services to the end users.

1. web server
2. app server
3. DB server

1. Web Server:
It is also called the presentation layer.
to show the application.
who works: ui/ux developers, frontend developers,
what they use: web technologies.
ex: html, css, js ....

2. App Server:
It is also called the logic layer.
to use the application.
who works: backend developers,
what they use: programming languages, frameworks.
ex: Java, PHP, Python....

3. DB Server:
It is also called the DB layer.
to store & retrieve data.
who works: DB admins,
what they use: DB languages.
ex: sql, oracle, postgres, arango ....

1. One-Tier: Standalone Application
The app will work on a local laptop.
All layers will be on locally.
It will not require an internet connection.
ex: VLC media player ...

2. Two-Tier: Client-Server Application
The app will work on a local laptop.
local: presentation, logic.  DB: internet
It will require an internet connection.
ex: Banking applications ...

3. Three-Tier: Web Application (RealTime)
Application does not need to be on local.
Everything we can use from the internet.
ex: WhatsApp, YouTube, Instagram...



  
